Workshop contingency planning:
- Container fallback for incompatible local environments
- Multi-stage build keeps image size manageable for slow networks
- Alpine base works on all architectures we target
- Health check enables Kubernetes/Swarm deployments

Security considerations:
- Non-root user prevents privilege escalation
- Minimal surface area with Alpine
- No sensitive data in image layers
- AWS credentials must be mounted, not baked in

Performance notes:
- Build cache important for workshop iterations
- Layer ordering optimizes for code changes
- Binary compilation in separate stage for caching
